# =============================================================================
# TRACKER OAUTH CONFIGURATION (OPTIONAL)
# =============================================================================
# 
# PyYomi uses the same approach as Mihon/Tachiyomi:
# - CLIENT_ID is embedded in the code (public by design)
# - No CLIENT_SECRET needed (uses PKCE for MAL, Implicit Grant for AniList)
# 
# You only need to set these if you want to use your own OAuth apps:
# 
# AniList: Register at https://anilist.co/settings/developer
#   - Use "Implicit Grant" flow (response_type=token)
#   - No client secret needed
# 
# MyAnimeList: Register at https://myanimelist.net/apiconfig
#   - Use PKCE flow (code_challenge)
#   - No client secret needed
# 
# =============================================================================

# Optional: Override default AniList CLIENT_ID
# ANILIST_CLIENT_ID=36426
# ANILIST_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/tracker/callback/anilist

# Optional: Override default MyAnimeList CLIENT_ID
# MAL_CLIENT_ID=your_mal_client_id
# MAL_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/tracker/callback/mal

# =============================================================================
# ENCRYPTION KEY (Auto-generated on first run if not set)
# =============================================================================
# Used for encrypting stored OAuth tokens in the database
# For production, set this to a secure random 32-byte base64 string
# Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
# ENCRYPTION_KEY=your_base64_encryption_key_here
